  india and bangladesh signed indiramujib agreement in 1974  we took 41 years to bring this issue to parliament and settle it whereas bangladesh ratified it in 1974 itself  the ministry of external affairs has taken the initiative in the able leadership of the hon minister of external affairs to achieve  this  result    india  and  bangladesh  do  not  have  many  disputes  one  was  3 bigha  corridor  issue  which  was  resolved  in  june  1992    we  want  good  relations with our neighbours  we should have increased border trade right from tripura to entire  northeast    we  need  to  increase  regional  cooperation    presently  there  is bombarding in many countries in asia  in such a time we are doing an agreement between  the  two  countries  and  our  parliament  is  passing  it    this  is  an  example before  the  world  people  mistake  human  problems  for  land  problems    but  the people in  enclaves had  many  issues relating  to  agriculture livelihood healthcare law  and  order  and  education    now  they  will  get  rid  of  these  problems    this  is only a beginning not an end  it is a reality that india had a partition  there is not point of return on it  but we can live as good neighbours with other countries    